name: The Woods
description:
Woodcut art, 2021.

At first sight, the place is read as calm and serene, completly far from the turbulent and unstable minds of megacities. The centenary trees, which live there, silently tell the stories of Judy, a woman excluded from society. The bad tongues say that she rides a broom in the dark, wearing faded clothes. She lives in the forest, as if this place were the last apocalyptic place in the world of terror and peace, two antagonisms present in the pagan wilderness.
